<html><head>
<title>Duplantier: TAX-FUNDED LOBBYING -- 4/15/96</title></head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/background.jpg">

<BLOCKQUOTE><BLOCKQUOTE><a href="/townhall/columnists/"><img align="right" vspace="10" src="/townhall/columnists/thcolm.gif"></a>
<B>BEHIND THE HEADLINES  </B><BR>
<i>Commentary from America's Future, Inc.   <br>

<a href="/townhall/columnists/duplbio.html">F.R. Duplantier</a><br>
April 15, 1996
</i><br>
<h2>
TAX-FUNDED LOBBYING
</h2>

<P><blockquote><i>  
Do you ever wonder where your federal income taxes go? Billions go to 
programs that subsidize special interest groups lobbying the government 
to increase spending! Consider the implications of that vicious circle 
when you file your 1040 today.
</blockquote></i>


<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
"The federal budget provides numerous slush funds that can be used to 
subsidize the lobbying and political activities of special-interest groups," reports Charles Griffin of the Heritage Foundation. "The agendas of these tax-subsidized groups tend toward bigger government, more spending,
and increased regulation. Every American is forced to finance this system 
that allows well-connected Washington-based groups to use taxpayer 
funds to advance political causes to which many Americans object."
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
AmeriCorps received $427 million from American taxpayers in 1995. 
Griffin claims that "several AmeriCorps programs have engaged in 
advocacy and direct partisan politics at the expense of the taxpayers," and 
in violation of the National and Community Service Trust Act of 1993. 
Also in 1995, the Legal Services Corporation funneled $400 million of 
our money to private groups that "engage in political and lobbying 
activities, often at the expense of the genuine legal services needed by the 
poor." Griffin describes the Legal Services Corporation as "the legal 
pillar of the welfare state," litigating and lobbying to expand the number 
of welfare recipients and drive up costs by "hundreds of billions of 
dollars."
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
Nearly $200 million was allocated for Title X Family Planning in 1995. 
"Despite the fact that much of Planned Parenthood's agenda is repulsive 
to large numbers of Americans," observes Griffin, "this high-profile 
political organization receives a substantial portion of its revenue each 
year" from programs administered under Title X. The National 
Endowment for the Humanities used the $180 million it received in 1995 
to promote "a liberal political and ideological agenda," says Griffin. 
"Abuse of federal grant dollars for political purposes is rampant in the 
National Endowment's most prominent current project, the so-called 
National Conversation. At the cost of millions of dollars, the endowment 
is subsidizing such special-interest groups as the National Council on 
Aging, the American Bar Association, and the American Library 
Association."
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
The $75 million allocated to the Market Promotion Program in 1995 for 
developing "commercial export markets for U.S. agricultural 
commodities" wound up in the hands of "some of the largest and most 
vocal special interests in the country," Griffin charges. Recipients of 
Market Promotion Program grants "opposed bipartisan efforts to reform 
farm subsidies. They fought successfully against the effort to eliminate 
[the Market Protection Program] outright, and they also fought reforms 
designed to decrease taxpayer subsidies to farmers, particularly large 
corporate farms. Once again, all of these self-serving efforts were 
subsidized unwittingly by the American taxpayer."
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
Griffin insists that "government funding of political activism is 
indefensible. Yet, hundreds of groups now receive government grants 
which are used, and used effectively, to subsidize their political 
activities." The question is, why do we put up with this outrage?

<P><P>

<i>
Behind The Headlines is produced by America's Future, a nonprofit 
educational organization dedicated to the preservation of our free-
enterprise system and our constitutional form of government. For a free 
transcript of this broadcast, send a self-addressed, stamped envelope to: 
America's Future, 7800 Bonhomme, St. Louis, Missouri 63105.
</i>

</blockquote></blockquote>




