<html><head>
<title>Duplantier: BIG GOVERNMENT THREATENS RIGHTS -- 4/17/96</title></head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/background.jpg">

<BLOCKQUOTE><BLOCKQUOTE><a href="/townhall/columnists/"><img align="right" vspace="10" src="/townhall/columnists/thcolm.gif"></a>
<B>BEHIND THE HEADLINES  </B><BR>
<i>Commentary from America's Future, Inc.   <br>

<a href="/townhall/columnists/duplbio.html">F.R. Duplantier</a><br>
April 17, 1996
</i><br>
<h2>
BIG GOVERNMENT THREATENS RIGHTS
</h2>

<P><blockquote><i>  
The Federal Government compels us to fork over fully one-third of our 
income, and it uses that money to infringe on the civil liberties protected 
by our Bill of Rights.
</blockquote></i>


<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
The First Amendment to the U.S. Constitution protects our right to 
practice our religious faith freely; and yet, the Supreme Court has often 
invoked this amendment to justify decisions restricting our freedom of 
religion. The nation's highest Court has prohibited the teaching of 
religion in public schools, as well as the recitation of prayers and the 
reading of the Bible.
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
The Second Amendment protects the right of the individual to own and 
make use of guns. Liberal politicians view gun ownership as an 
interference with the expansion of federal power, which of course it is, 
for an armed citizenry is much more difficult to subjugate than one 
without weapons. Those who don't like the Second Amendment exploit 
every public tragedy involving firearms as propaganda for tighter 
restrictions on their use.
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
Our right to privacy, protected by the Third and Fourth Amendments, is 
also under attack. The Federal Government seems determined to increase 
its control over all of us by prying into our daily lives. Tax collectors and 
regulatory agents have been snooping on us for years; and now, in the 
name of combating terrorism, the President demands wiretapping 
privileges for federal agents to investigate any suspected felony. There 
are 1,300 federal felonies. You could be guilty of one right now without 
even knowing it.
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
The Fifth Amendment not only protects us against double jeopardy and 
self-incrimination; it also prohibits the confiscation of our property by the 
Federal Government without proper compensation. Yet, today, 
Americans frequently find their property devalued by governmental 
edicts restricting the use of it -- or even taken from them altogether in the 
interest of some putative public good.
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
The Sixth Amendment guarantees our right to a trial by jury in a criminal 
case. How juries are selected and instructed, however, often determines 
how effective they are. Unfortunately, jurors are routinely screened on 
the basis of their philosophical or religious beliefs, and those who show 
any propensity for questioning the evidence in the case or the validity of 
the law are usually dismissed posthaste. The Seventh Amendment 
protects our right to a trial by jury in a civil suit, but the growth of 
regulatory agencies has enabled unelected bureaucrats to bypass that 
safeguard -- and instead act as prosecutor, judge, and jury. There are over 
13 million federal bureaucrats meddling in the daily affairs of American 
citizens.
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
Some federal judges and regulatory agents simply disregard the Eighth 
Amendment, which prohibits unreasonable fines and punishments. Some 
also ignore the Ninth and Tenth Amendments, which stipulate that the 
people and the States reserve to themselves all rights not expressly 
granted to the Federal Government. One thing is clear: If Americans want 
to retain the liberties protected by our Bill of Rights, we'd better make our 
voices heard.
<P><P>

<i>
Behind The Headlines is produced by America's Future, a nonprofit 
educational organization dedicated to the preservation of our free-
enterprise system and our constitutional form of government. For a free 
transcript of this broadcast, send a self-addressed, stamped envelope to: 
America's Future, 7800 Bonhomme, St. Louis, Missouri 63105.
</i>

</blockquote></blockquote>




