HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Server: Netscape-Commerce/1.12
Date: Wednesday, 08-Jan-97 21:05:47 GMT
Last-modified: Tuesday, 04-Jun-96 20:07:14 GMT
Content-length: 4520
Content-type: text/html
</DOCHDR>
<html><head>
<title>Duplantier: REP. SMITH ON CHINA -- 4/24/96</title></head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/background.jpg">

<BLOCKQUOTE><BLOCKQUOTE><a href="/townhall/columnists/"><img align="right" vspace="10" src="/townhall/columnists/thcolm.gif"></a>
<B>BEHIND THE HEADLINES  </B><BR>
<i>Commentary from America's Future, Inc.   <br>

<a href="/townhall/columnists/duplbio.html">F.R. Duplantier</a><br>
April 24, 1996
</i><br>
<h2>
REP. SMITH ON CHINA
</h2>

<P><blockquote><i>  
During hearings last May on the coercive population control program 
that Communist China has conducted for at least two decades, the 
chairman of a House Subcommittee posed the question. Should such a 
monstrous abuse of human rights affect our relations with that barbaric 
country?
</blockquote></i>

<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
Congressman Christopher Smith, chairman of the House Subcommittee 
on International Operations and Human Rights, began his opening 
remarks by noting that Communist China "routinely compels women to 
abort their 'unauthorized' unborn children. The usual method," he 
observed, "is intense 'persuasion' using all of the economic, social, and 
psychological tools a totalitarian State has at its disposal. When these 
methods fail, the woman is taken physically to the abortion mill. Forced 
abortions are often performed very late in pregnancy, even in the ninth 
month." The final indignity is forced sterilization for the woman or her 
husband.
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
"Forced abortion was properly considered a crime against humanity at the 
Nuremberg war crimes tribunal," Congressman Smith continued. "It is 
employed regularly with chilling effectiveness and unbearable pain upon 
women in the People's Republic of China. Women in China are required 
to obtain a birth coupon before conceiving a child. Chinese women are 
hounded by the population control police and even their menstrual cycles 
are publicly monitored as one means of ensuring compliance. "
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
Congressman Smith reported that the communist government in China 
has recently "issued a new law on eugenics which is now taking effect 
and which nationalizes discrimination against the handicapped. In a move 
that is eerily reminiscent of Nazi Germany, the Communist Chinese 
Government is implementing forced abortion against handicapped 
children and forced sterilization against parents who simply do not 
measure up in the eyes of the State. Despite all of this," said Smith, "the 
United Nations Population Fund continues to provide funds, materiel, 
people [and the] shield of respectability that the Chinese program so 
desperately wants."
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
Smith chastised the head of the UN Population Fund for insisting that 
China's birth control program is voluntary. "This is unmitigated nonsense 
and a big lie," said the congressman. "Degrading a few men, women, and 
children may be of no great matter for the Chinese communist regime, 
which has long regarded homicide and torture as among the basic tools of 
statecraft," conceded Smith, but that doesn't explain the willingness of 
Westerners to overlook -- or even facilitate -- such abuses. "So the most 
shocking thing about forced abortions and sterilization in China is not 
that they happen," said Smith, "but that otherwise humane societies such 
as the United States might forcibly return people who have managed to 
escape from them."
<BR>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
This is exactly what our current government has done. "The Clinton 
administration, which campaigned on a human rights platform that was 
justly critical of some of the refugee policies of its predecessors," said 
Smith, "quickly reversed course and began mass forcible repatriations of 
people who had escaped from China." The President has thus made the 
American people a party to the slaughter of innocents in China.
<P><P>

<i>
Behind The Headlines is produced by America's Future, a nonprofit 
educational organization dedicated to the preservation of our free-
enterprise system and our constitutional form of government. For a free 
transcript of this broadcast, send a self-addressed, stamped envelope to: 
America's Future, 7800 Bonhomme, St. Louis, Missouri 63105.
</i>

</blockquote></blockquote>




