<html>
<head>
<title>Duplantier: TRUTH ABOUT COMMUNISM -- 6/04/96</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/background.jpg">

<BLOCKQUOTE><BLOCKQUOTE>
<a href="/townhall/columnists/"><img align="right" vspace="10" src="/townhall/columnists/thcolm.gif">
</a><b>BEHIND THE HEADLINES</b><BR>

<i>
Commentary from America's Future, Inc.<br>

<a href="/townhall/columnists/duplbio.html">F.R. Duplantier</a><br>
June 04, 1996<br><p></i>
<h2> Truth About Communism </h2>


<i><blockquote>



John T. Flynn did not have access to the Venona documents, but he did 
have plenty of other evidence, when he tried to convince his skeptical 
countrymen of the truly insidious nature of the Communist conspiracy.
</blockquote></i><P>

John T. Flynn knew that "one of the greatest difficulties in explaining 
this menace is the inability of the normal, decent American to fully 
understand the peculiar nature of Communist methods." Nevertheless, in 
a nationally syndicated radio broadcast in 1954, Flynn charged that 
"among us is a sizable number of people [who] hate our American way. 
They want to end our free system and introduce a system more nearly 
resembling that of Russia. The State . . . will be supreme. It will own all 
the large industries . . . and, eventually, everything. This is socialism."
<BR> 
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

Flynn pointed out that Communists "seldom get elected to office. They 
cannot get power to act, at least not so long as they admit they are 
Communists. So their policy is to deny they are Communists or socialists 
and to insert themselves into influential positions in the Democratic or 
Republican parties and to get into bureaus where decisions on policy are 
made." Once they've weaseled their way in, "they use their weight to 
influence those policies of the government which will serve their ends 
and the ends of Soviet Russia."
<BR> 
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

Flynn charged that "secret cells began to operate in the important 
agencies of our government" in 1933. By the time of his broadcast, 
eleven years later, "thousands of these Reds had made their way into 
almost all of the most important spots in our government." Ensconced in 
positions of influence, "they took their orders directly from agents of the 
Russian espionage system stationed in New York and Washington."
<BR> 
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

The alarming extent of this penetration of our government was "brought 
out in a series of investigations in which the members of the House and 
the Senate who made the investigations were pilloried and denounced by 
the same newspapers and political leaders who [later denounced] Senator 
Joseph McCarthy. It was the influence of these cells which enabled the 
Soviet government, when World War II ended, to take over all of Eastern 
Europe and most of the continent of Asia, to penetrate our colleges, our 
public school system, many of our leading magazines and newspapers 
and news services."
<BR> 
&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

Flynn recalled Senator McCarthy's famous 1950 speech in which "he 
charged that Communists in the State Department were helping to shape 
our policy in Asia and he put the number of Communists in a position to 
do this at 57. But he did not name them publicly. For this and a 
subsequent speech he was greeted by a storm of abuse." Flynn argued 
that "it takes a brave man to stand up against the savage abuse and the 
underground assaults which these Red conspirators pour out upon any 
loyal American who attempts to oppose them." He expressed intense 
admiration for "the undaunted stand [McCarthy took] against the 
malignant defenders of Russia and their confederates and dupes in the 
United States."

<P><P>

<i>
Behind The Headlines is produced by America's Future, a nonprofit 
educational organization dedicated to the preservation of our free-
enterprise system and our constitutional form of government. For a free 
transcript of this broadcast, send a self-addressed, stamped envelope to: 
America's Future, 7800 Bonhomme, St. Louis, Missouri 63105
</i>

</blockquote></blockquote>




