<html><head><title>Duplantier:  THE ENDURING WISDOM OF JOHN T. FLYNN</title></head><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/background.jpg"><a href="/townhall/columnists/"><img align="right" vspace="10" src="/townhall/columnists/thcolm.gif"></a><center><h4>BEHIND THE HEADLINES </h4><i>Commentary from America's Future, Inc.<br><a href="/townhall/columnists/duplbio.html">F.R. Duplantier</a> <br>November 17, 1995 <br></i><hr><h2>The Enduring Wisdom of John T. Flynn</h2></center><P>


[Noted journalist and author John T. Flynn warned more than 50 years 
ago that America was headed down "the road to Socialism. " His 
recommendations for averting disaster are just as valid today as they 
were then.]
<p>
In a book called The Road Ahead, published decades ago, the late John 
T. Flynn argued that Americans committed to fighting the creeping 
advance of socialism in our country must first "rid themselves of the 
moral intimidation which has been imposed on their minds." An excerpt 
from that book appears in a new compilation of Flynn's writing entitled 
Forgotten Lessons. published by the Foundation for Economic 
Education. Flynn noted that "the American system has been painted as 
something wicked. bungling. even brutal. while the Planned New World 
of the future will be filled with sweetness, light, and plenty." This false 
picture has had an impact not only on naive Americans, but also on 
those who ought to know better.
<p>
John T. Flynn observed that the choice before us is not "between a 
perfect system called Socialism and an imperfect system called 
Capitalism. It is a choice between two human systems both of which will 
inevitably have their imperfections because they are human. But the 
Socialist Planners do not concede this. Capitalism they present to us only 
in terms of its defects. But Socialism is painted only in terms of the 
wonderful things it is going to do some day." Citing the disastrous effects 
of Socialism in Russia. Germany. Italy. and Britain. Flynn reminded his 
readers that "the greatest and most efficient producing machine in the 
world is in [America]. This did not happen by accident " he asserted. "It 
is the result of the soil of freedom in which it grew."
<p>
Socialism was far advanced in America even in Flys day, and it has 
gained ground since then. Fort years later we are still confronted with 
the need to counteract what Fly called "the social disease that is 
destroying us." Flynn urged his countrymen to "stop apologizing for our 
Capitalist society." We should take no more steps down the road to 
Socialism. he said. and we should turn out of office any politician who 
tries to lead us in that direction. Flynn pointed out. Iong before Dan 
Quayle and Pat Buchanan. "that we are in a social war. and that we must 
fight it as such." He said we should "put an end to the orgy of spending 
that is rapidly bankrupt the nation," quit trying to plan our economy, and 
instead let "our free system of private enterprise operate at its fullest 
capacity."
<p>
John T. Flynn was a founding member of America's Future, the producer 
of this series of broadcasts, and a man of great wisdom and vision. Flynn 
advised his readers to rediscover their principles in the U.S. 
Constitution. the Declaration of Independence, and American history -- 
and use those principles "to dismantle the tyrant State in America and to 
build up once again the energies of a free people."
<p>                           <P><i>Behind The Headlines is produced by America's Future, a nonprofit educational organization dedicated to the preservation of our free enterprise system and our constitutional form of government. For a free transcript of this broadcast, write: America's Future, 7800 Bonhomme, St. Louis, Missouri 63105.</i><p><br><br><center><br><a href="/townhall/tbut.map"><img src="/townhall/tbut.gif" ismap border="0"></a></center></body></html>
